race.comment: SHALHAVMUSIK (9) is a maiden facing some better-performed horses here but she does look well placed to go close to winning. She put the writing on the wall with a head-turning run in a city maiden first-up and is placed second-up previously. With a low draw, she maps to get a cosy run for Holder and she will be in the finish with some luck. BELLE INFERNO (1) gets in well after the claim. She was fair first-up for the stable and if she can recapture her best Victorian form, she's a danger. DARRA LINEN (10) boasts a poor winning strike rate but has run quite a few good races this campaign. Kelvin Bourke has enjoyed success campaigning his horses in SA so respect the placement. GRANDELLIE (8) is next in line.
